latestIgtvVideos.title: Buddhist Prayer spinning wheels in Dehradun Mindrolling Monastery
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
These are Tibetan Buddhist prayer wheels and they often have 'Om mani padme hum' engraved on them:

According to Tibetan Buddhist belief, spinning a prayer wheel is just as effective as reciting the sacred texts aloud. This belief derives from the Buddhist belief in the power of sound and the formulas to which deities are subject. For many Buddhists, the prayer wheel also represents the Wheel of the Law (or Dharma) set in motion by the Buddha.

Here's the link to the whole Dehradun trip:
https://youtu.be/GgWZh1XFweE

latestPosts.caption:
Throwback to the day when I met PC @priyankachopra 😇 3 years ago, I moved to Mumbai with nothing but dreams (and a ring light 😄). I was already making beauty videos, but something about this city made me go all in. I started taking content creation seriously, and slowly, my little online fam started growing💗

With that came opportunities — unpaid and paid both. But this particular opportunity is something I’ll forever cherish.

I was one of the few creators selected to meet her. I got to spend a few magical moments with her, click pictures, and (my fav part) get her book signed — something no one else thought of doing at the event 😄📖💫

Do you know how I greeted her?
I said: Hi Priyanka, I’m Priyanka 🤩
And she said: Hi Priyanka 😀

Manifestation? Hard work? Mumbai magic? Maybe all of it. But one thing I know — this was a moment I’ll never forget. 🤍
#Grateful #BeautyCreator #DreamsComeTrue #MumbaiDiaries
